-----------------------------------------
Sparse notes on A/V Resources management.
-----------------------------------------

* Default dir for A/V files is /var/fenice/avroot.
* Default RTSP port is 554.

* For every A/V resource you need
  
  1) Either separate files for audio (MP3) and video (MPEG-1,2), or a
     libavformat compatible container (mov/mp4 suggested)
  2) a Source Description (.sd) file for resource description to map the
     different sources.
  
  Streming clients must be invoked with, e.g:
  	
	$ mystreamingclient rtsp://streamingserver/myvideo.sd

  or similar. 
  You can't request plain files as you would expect from a webserver.
  
  See test files in avroot dir for examples.

* You can do live streaming using a named-pipe:

  1) Create a named-pipe (e.g., mkfifo live.mp3),
  2) create an .sd file with the named-pipe as audio content, then
  3) feed named-pipe with live-encoded mp3 data.

  You may use the felix companion tool to ease the live stream management.

* Suggested encoding tools:
  Video: mjpegtools' mpeg2enc, ffmpeg
  Audio: lame, ffmpeg
